AU Commission Chair Moussa Faki Mahamat says at least $50 billion of illicit money flows out of Africa every year. PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa is in Mauritania for the 31st African Union summit. The theme is fighting the corruption hamstringing development. AU Commission Chair Moussa Faki Mahamat says at least $50 billion of illicit money flows out of Africa every year. That’s enough to lift countries out of poverty and change the lives of million of Africans. Dealing with this is a priority of the gathering in Nouakchott this weekend. But leaders also have to look at sustaining the peace signed between South Sudan’s government and the rebels who’s five-year war as killed a hundred thousand and displaced millions. They also have to press new member Morocco to end its illegal occupation of the Western Sahara which is Africa’s last colonial vestige.